This approach is not robust enough. A better approach is to directly prove the matrix equality by showing that for any indices `i, j`, the `(i, j)` entry of the matrix on the left equals the `(i, j)` entry of the matrix on the right. This can be done using `ext i j`, then `simp` to expand definitions, and then `norm_num` and `ring_nf` to simplify the resulting expressions. The condition `i = j` will also need to be handled.

