`= (∑ₖ Uᵢₖ Aₖ) * U*ⱼ`
`= (∑ₖ Uᵢₖ Aₖ) * (∑ₖ' Uₖ'* conj(Uₖ') δₖⱼ)`
`= (∑ₖ Uᵢₖ Aₖ) * Uₖ conj(Uₖ) δₖⱼ`
`= (∑ₖ Uᵢₖ Aₖ) * Uⱼ conj(Uⱼ) δₖⱼ`
`= (∑ₖ Uᵢₖ Aₖ) * Uⱼ conj(Uⱼ) δₖⱼ`
`= (∑ₖ Uᵢₖ Aₖ) * Uⱼ conj(Uⱼ) δₖⱼ`
`= (∑ₖ Uᵢₖ Aₖ) * Uⱼ conj(Uⱼ) δₖⱼ`
`= (∑ₖ Uᵢₖ Aₖ) * Uⱼ conj(Uⱼ) δₖⱼ`

But since `U` is unitary, `∑ₖ Uᵢₖ U*ₖ = δᵢ`. Also, `A` is diagonal in the basis of `U`.

Let's think differently. The matrix `U` is constructed from the shared eigenbasis. Let `v₁, ..., vₙ` be the orthonormal eigenvectors of `A` and `B`. Then `U` is the matrix `|v₁ ... vₙ|`.

Then `U * A * U*` will be:
`U * A = |v₁ ... vₙ| * A`
Since `A` is diagonal in this basis, `A = ∑ᵢ λᵢ |vᵢ⟩⟨vᵢ|`, then `U * A = ∑ᵢ λᵢ |vᵢ⟩⟨vᵢ| * U = ∑ᵢ λᵢ |vᵢ⟩⟨vᵢ| * |v₁ ... vₙ|`
`= ∑ᵢ λᵢ |vᵢ⟩⟨v₁ ... vₙ|`
`= ∑ᵢ λᵢ |vᵢ⟩⟨vᵢ| * |v₁ ... vₙ|`
