1. Find the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of A
2. Find the eigenvalues and eigenvectors of B
3. Construct a basis that is a union of eigenvectors of A and B
4. This basis will be orthonormal since A and B are Hermitian
5. The matrix U will be the matrix whose columns are the vectors from this basis

